docs.lead_paragraph: At some point during Netflix’s “Sense8” — a gorgeous, ridiculous series about eight strangers scattered across the world who use a psychic connection to aid one another in fights and at one point have a virtual orgy — I had to ask myself: What am I watching?

headline.main: Streaming TV Isn’t Just a New Way to Watch. It’s a New Genre.

docs.abstract: The Haggler tries to get to the bottom of where fake online product reviews originate. One notable source seems to be the website Fiverr.
docs.snippet: The Haggler tries to get to the bottom of where fake online product reviews originate. One notable source seems to be the website Fiverr.
docs.lead_paragraph: The holiday online shopping season has begun, and that means reading lots of online product reviews. Some of these reviews are helpful, others are not. And many are fakes — raves or pans from people who have never actually used the product. Where do fake reviews come from? In this column, a close-up look at one notable source.

headline.main: All the Product Reviews Money Can Buy

docs.lead_paragraph: On the community desk, we like to say that comments enhance the news. But sometimes, the comments are the news. Such was the case this year when an exposé became the most commented-on news story in Times history (that story is revealed below). Also this year: One of our top commenters upstaged his famous sibling and another became a celebrity in his hometown. To see which stories resonated most with our readers, you need look no further. docs.abstract: This comedy-drama on Amazon broadens its focus beyond Jeffrey Tambor’s character, Maura, to include the family’s children, in-laws, exes and long-gone ancestors.
docs.snippet: This comedy-drama on Amazon broadens its focus beyond Jeffrey Tambor’s character, Maura, to include the family’s children, in-laws, exes and long-gone ancestors.
docs.lead_paragraph: “What is being queer if not questioning everything?” asks Ali Pfefferman (Gaby Hoffmann), during an argument with her lover. Ali, who may be attracted to another woman, argues that she wants to avoid forcing a “heteronormative” model on their relationship. Her lover suggests that Ali, who only recently came out, is being perhaps a little self-serving. “Listen to yourself,” she says. “You’ve been queer for, like, 30 seconds.”

headline.main: Season 2 of ‘Transparent’ Expands Its View of the Pfefferman Clan
